<lesson><title>24. How many people? 1-3, many.</title>

<designnote>This lesson introduces counting (of people), using only			the minimum numbers/amounts (1, 2, 3, many) needed to show the basics			of the system.			Image files simply show these numbers: X number of countables together,			either as a natural picture or a photoshopping of X number of			identical images.		</designnote><explnote>In this lesson, we learn to count people: asking how many,					and giving answers.	</explnote><timesig>@20120723-JW-RM-1thru25.wav@8:31-8:57</timesig>		
